VAfghanistan looks so different from here in America.
p141
aVI find that Americans see the fragility in changes.
p142
aVI fear that these changes will not last
p143
aVmuch beyond the U.S. troops' withdrawal.
p144
aVBut when I am back in Afghanistan,
p145
aVwhen I see the students in my school
p146
aVand their parents who advocate for them,
p147
aVwho encourage them, I see a promising future
p148
aVand lasting change.
p149
aVTo me, Afghanistan is a country of hope and boundless possibilities,
p150
aVand every single day
p151
aVthe girls of SOLA remind me of that.
p152
aVLike me, they are dreaming big.
